The paper deals with the computational complexity of finding pure Nash equilibria in graphical games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves analyzing the structure of graphs and hypergraphs, which falls under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper uses complexity theoretic assumptions and techniques such as homomorphism problems, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
